  "texts": [
    "The parameter A L serves as an estimate of the delensing fraction; the results of A L in Table 2 and Table 3 align well with the outcomes depicted in Fig. 7 and Fig.",
    "8 respectively.",
    "For the satellite experiment, the delensing process leads to a reduction in σ(r) from 0.504 × 10 -3 to 0.187 × 10 -3, corresponding to a reduction of approximately ∼ 63%.",
    "Similar reductions in σ(r) due to delensing are observed in other experiments, with around a 46% reduction in the gSAT+gLAT experiment.Although map-based delensing process (L1) is beneficial in reducing σ(r), it introduces bias on r. From Fig. 7, we observe that the delensing fractions does not remain constant, while we incorporate this variability by fitting them with a floating constant parameter A L in our model.",
    "As we mentioned in Section 4.4, we notice that the delensing fractions become more uniform in Fig. 8 after separating the delensing noise bias N del ℓ, leading us to expect a reduction in the bias on r. The result in Table 3 also support that including N del ℓ in the model (L2) contributes to a reduction in the bias on r compared with model (L1).One can see that from model L2 to model L1, the bias on r is significantly reduced, about 88% for the ground experiments and 71% for the satellite one."
